Another challenge
A big wood ball covered in holes, one ball for each team, a tower at the other end of river, a tower at the other end of the river. The holes are about the size of a finger, character can look inside. The cloths in the sphere otherwise don't get removed.

Inside there a cloth bundles matching the color of the towers, the sphere has to be moved across the river, there are also cloth bundles in the tower. There are several matching cloth bundles, they need to get/find all the matching cloth bundles, and bring the ball back to starting point with all the matching cloths.

This challenge is an homage to the historical Pre-Columbian "Stone Spheres" (Isla del Caño).

OPEN QUESTION: how big are the wooden spheres?
